==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek ''dys-'' ([[bad]] or [[ill]]) + ''plas(is)'', from ''plassein'' (to [[mold]]) + ''-ia'', (a formative ending used in Greek)

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/dɪs.pleɪ'.ʒʌ/}}, {{AHD|/dĭs-plā'zhə/}}, {{SAMPA|/dIs=ple"=ZV/}}

===Noun===
'''dysplasia'''

# {{pathology}} [[abnormal|Abnormal]] [[development]] of [[cell]]s or [[tissue]], often a [[precancerous]] stage of [[growth]].

